node.text:
This spectacular 1.6 acre property rests high above the glistening waters of the Long Island Sound and Larchmont Harbor, with over 500 ft of private shoreline, a deep water dock, a jetty, and an area for swimming or launching a small watercraft. Magnificently sited on a lush promontory adjacent to Manor Park, this beautiful 8,182 SF, 1898 Victorian is designed to highlight the gorgeous panoramas from every room. Experience unobstructed views from the wraparound porch, bluestone patio, in-ground pool & spa. An original stable is now a 3 bed, 2 bath guest house with chic-retro kitchen. At the heart of this 3-level turreted icon is a great room that soars 2 stories with stairway to a glass cupola. Each space melds period grandeur with glamour. This home is unrivaled.
25 Park Avenue, Larchmont, NY $11,300,000
7 Bedrooms
6/2 Baths
Don’t miss out on the opportunity to own this extraordinary waterfront home, listed with @Mimi.Magarelli. Learn more via the link below.
https://wpsir.co/25ParkAvenue
 
 #JBFSIRListings #JBFSIRLarchmont #JBFSIRWestchesterCounty #BeyondTheCity #JBFSIR # SothebysRealty #WestchesterCounty

Welcome to this historic Westport home.
Once, in Old Westport, there was a charming boat club on the Sherwood Mill Pond. It was sited on a 1.9 acre point with 180’ of breathtaking unobstructed water views. Over time, with care and architectural integrity, the property has evolved into a well loved and tended home with gracious spaces, style, comfort and unequaled water views. Extensively enlarged and remodeled in 1989, and true to tradition the original clubhouse is the one you want to come home to. Enter through the roses and rhododendrons on the flagstone path to the gracious front entry foyer into the jaw dropping great room, anchored by the original stone fireplace with views of the pond along an entire window wall. On a summer day, after tennis on the court, walk the path to the pool, or canoe on the pond. The privacy is enviable, the home, gracious and warm, the views breathtaking.
